						               													<description>It was used in a giant size in 1984 in the Spanish most famous TV contest &amp;quot;Un, dos, tres... responda otra vez&amp;quot; (on which the British &amp;quot;Three, two, one&amp;quot; was based)and shortly later comerciallized as a board game for the general public.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game about moving pawns through a locker until you reach the end of the course or fall eliminated. Slightly based on the Game of the Goose.&amp;#10;The route has bifurcations, and each square has different effects: the highlighted &amp;quot;La Ch&amp;aacute;rcel&amp;quot;, which obligates the player to answer a question or to do a try-out the first time or stop playing; &amp;quot;El Chobst&amp;aacute;culo&amp;quot;, like the previous one but with two opportunities; &amp;quot;El Saltichollo&amp;quot;, with similar effect to the Goose; and &amp;quot;The Retrochollo&amp;quot;, similar to the previous one, but backwards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Se utiliz&amp;oacute; en un formato gigante en 1984 en el concurso de TV &amp;quot;Un, dos, tres... responda otra vez&amp;quot;, para ser comercializado al poco tiempo como juego de mesa para el p&amp;uacute;blico general.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Juego de mover fichas por un casillero hasta llegar al final del recorrido o caer eliminado. Ligeramente basado en el Juego de la Oca. &amp;#10;El recorrido ten&amp;iacute;a bifurcaciones, y cada casilla ten&amp;iacute;a efectos diferentes. Destacaban &amp;quot;La Ch&amp;aacute;rcel&amp;quot;, que obligaba a contestar una pregunta o hacer una prueba a la primera o dejar de jugar, &amp;quot;El Chobst&amp;aacute;culo&amp;quot;, igual que la anterior pero con dos oportunidades, &amp;quot;El Saltichollo&amp;quot;, con efecto similar a la oca, y &amp;quot;El Retrochollo&amp;quot;, similar a la anterior, pero hacia atr&amp;aacute;s.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
